\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104myh1665702957885.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/myh1665702957885.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/myh1665702957885.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"myh1665702957885\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      step size\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the step size for the Uniface stepped hitlist mechanism.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"myh1665702957885__topic_d55991e1_d55992e1_d55993e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"myh1665702957885__p_d55994e1_d55995e1_d55996e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$ORA_PARAMS = step size</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Number</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"myh1665702957885__p_d55997e1_d55998e1_d55999e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$ORA_PARAMS = ss</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Number</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"myh1665702957885__section_v4c_yp4_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1218401e72\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"myh1665702957885__p_d56003e1_d56004e1_d56005e1\">This option specifies the step size of the Uniface\n            stepped hitlist mechanism. The number specified must be in the range from 0 through\n            32,767. If you specify 0, the stepped hitlist mechanism is disabled, causing Uniface to\n            internally finish the hitlist each time, before returning control to the\n            application.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"myh1665702957885__p_d56006e1_d56007e1_d56008e1\">The actual step size used is always either zero or a\n            multiple of the actual array fetch size. When necessary, Uniface uses the smallest step\n            size greater than or equal to the specified step size which is a multiple of the array\n            size. To avoid confusion, specify a step size which is either zero or a multiple of the\n            specified array size.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"myh1665702957885__p_d56009e1_d56010e1_d56011e1\">When the <code class=\"ph codeph\">fixed array size</code> option is\n            set, and the recommended step size is a multiple of the array fetch size, the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">array fetch size</code> option only affects the performance of the\n            application, and not the behavior. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">step size</code> option, on the other\n            hand, determines how many records are processed before control returns to the\n            application. This affects, for example, the behavior of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$curhits</code>\n            variable.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gwm1665702661923.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Stepped Hitlists</a><p>Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. This mechanism ensures that a limited number of occurrences are fetched from the database, even though a large number of occurrences match the retrieve profile entered by the user.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxl1665702732616.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>fixed array size</a><p>Use exact array size specified by array fetch size. Do not increase array size for small records.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530133\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530133\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "step size Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 step size Set the step size for the Uniface stepped hitlist mechanism. USYS$ORA_PARAMS = step size Number USYS$ORA_PARAMS = ss Number Description This option specifies the step size of the Uniface stepped hitlist mechanism. The number specified must be in the range from 0 through 32,767. If you specify 0, the stepped hitlist mechanism is disabled, causing Uniface to internally finish the hitlist each time, before returning control to the application. The actual step size used is always either zero or a multiple of the actual array fetch size. When necessary, Uniface uses the smallest step size greater than or equal to the specified step size which is a multiple of the array size. To avoid confusion, specify a step size which is either zero or a multiple of the specified array size. When the fixed array size option is set, and the recommended step size is a multiple of the array fetch size, the array fetch size option only affects the performance of the application, and not the behavior. The step size option, on the other hand, determines how many records are processed before control returns to the application. This affects, for example, the behavior of the $curhits variable. Related Links Stepped Hitlists Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. This mechanism ensures that a limited number of occurrences are fetched from the database, even though a large number of occurrences match the retrieve profile entered by the user. fixed array size Use exact array size specified by array fetch size. Do not increase array size for small records. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}